Um... I'm okay with that kind of thing...
\n<Minato>Well, in that case...
...Saying that, she quickly left.
\n<Minato>「！？」
I overtook her and confronted her again.

\n<\N[5]>I'm definitely not a suspicious person...
And it's not like I'm trying to hit on
her or anything...

I start to panic as I fumble with the
pockets of my jacket, searching for my
business card holder, but I can't find
it anywhere and I become flustered.
\n<Minato>...A novice performer?

\n<\N[5]>No, that's not it! Huh? That's strange... I
always keep it in my inner pocket,
but... Ah!

\n<\N[5]>Damn it... Today was supposed to be my day
off... I left my business card holder at
the hotel...

I remember that it was my first day off
since coming on a business trip, and I
was taking a leisurely solo trip around
the station. It seems that... I was
getting excited by this unexpected
reunion.
\n<Minato>...Well, you do your best too.
She tapped my shoulder and ran away...

\n<\N[5]>(Well... Unlike last time when things were
hectic, this time I have plenty of time,
so there should be plenty of
opportunities)

\n<\N[5]>(Next, I'll follow the proper procedure...
Huh?)

I can feel the gazes from the people
around me. Well, of course... from their
perspective, it must look like a failed
attempt at picking up someone. Standing
there alone, I must look quite
ridiculous.

\n<\N[5]>(No, I'm not trying to pick someone up...
Please don't look at me like that...)

And... unable to bear it any longer, I fled
from that place as if running away...

Four months ago... When I was staying at the
business trip destination for about
three days for various procedures, I met
her.

...I really fell in love at first sight. I
happened to see her playing the guitar
in front of the station, and I just
stopped my feet for some reason because
of my job. But... before I knew it, I
was captivated.

Just like me, the people who were touched by
her music also stopped in their tracks
as the snow began to fall in the cold
sky... Everyone was captivated by her
singing.

... I closed my eyes. And then... I could
clearly picture you singing in front of
a large crowd.

I was so embarrassed that I couldn't tell
you in the end, but at that time... I
had a premonition of your shining
future, .

I wonder what she is doing now? Is she
lying down on the same bed? And... I
hope she is sleeping peacefully.

Even though we were always together, now it
feels like we can't be. Even though we
are in the same mansion, I feel a
distance greater than just physical
distance.

I want to meet and talk... Now... I feel
like I can say it now. You, who shines
brighter day by day, are too dazzling
for someone like me... I have words that
I couldn't convey because of my
inferiority complex.
Since that time, I have always...

\n<\N[5]>Wow... That's amazing. It seems like it can
earn quite a lot.

Minato, who had thrown the tip into the empty
tip jar and finished preparing to leave,
stood up.
\n<Minato>Hehe, today we'll have croquettes for dinner.
\n<\N[5]>Huh... You seem quite desperate...

\n<Minato>Because most of my part-time job earnings go
towards funding our activities...

Well, that's true... There are instrument
maintenance costs and box fees.
Generally, there is a perception that
student band members are poor.
Especially since she was living alone,
it was even more so.
\n<\N[5]>......Shall we go grab a meal?

I couldn't help but feel sorry for her
dinner situation, so I unintentionally
invited her. I really didn't mean
anything else, but I guess it can't be
helped if it's perceived that way.
\n<Minato>What?! Of course, I'll treat you!

...I was surprised when Minato unexpectedly
got on, but I was relieved that she
didn't think I was trying to pick her
up. I wonder if I've been able to gain
her trust by hiding my identity and
going there for almost a year?
\n<Minato>Hey... Can I choose the restaurant?
\n<\N[5]>Hmm... Ah, I don't mind...

\n<\N[5]>(Well... If I think of it as a commemoration of
realizing that I have gained her trust,
this level of expense is cheap.)

I don't really have a significant
income... But thanks to not having any
hobbies and not being very
materialistic, I had some savings.

So I was feeling bold. I was looking
forward to seeing what kind of famous
restaurant she would take me to.
\n<Minato>Hehe, it's been a while since I've eaten out♪

\n<\N[5]>(What... what is this girl... coming to make me
cry?)

\n<\N[5]>Um... Is it okay? Since it's a special
occasion, maybe we should go to a local
restaurant known for its delicious
food...
\n<Minato>Hmm... What's wrong? Let's go already!

\n<\N[5]>(Well... I like it too, but I go there 2-3 times
a week...)

\n<Minato>There are so many options... I'm not sure
what to choose...

Minato, with a frown on her face, was staring
intently at the menu. She seemed to be
struggling with what to eat.

\n<Minato>The set meals are tempting, but I feel like
I've become a gyudon mouth...

\n<\N[5]>It seems like you can also choose the
toppings.
\n<Minato>What... what did you say... nuguuuguu...

...It seems like it will take a while longer.
I took out my smartphone and decided to
kill time for now.

\n<Minato>Alright, I've decided on the large serving of
gyudon. Simple is best. \N[5]-san, what
are you going to order?

\n<\N[5]>I'll go with the regular... Oh, maybe I'll
add an egg too.

\n<Minato>...Huh? Are you saying I should line up... for
a regular- sized gyudon?
\n<\N[5]>Eh... well... then, let's call the waiter.
\n<Minato>Wait a minute!

Minato, with a fierce expression, grabbed my
hand as I reached for the call button.

\n<Minato>\N[5]-san, are you going for the large serving?
You're a bit on the slim side, so you
should eat a lot...

\n<\N[5]>Why is that? I always get the regular size.
Just let go... Huh?! What strength...

...Minato's fingertips sank into the back of my
hand. Just before pressing the button,
my hand stopped and couldn't move even a
bit.
\n<\N[5]>Ouch... It would be bad if I left a mark...
\n<Minato>But...

\n<\N[5]>The waiter doesn't really care about that
kind of thing...

\n<Minato>I'll take care of the order because it
matters to me.

\n<Minato>One large serving and one extra-large
serving of beef bowl with two eggs. Oh,
and also one regular serving for
takeout, please.
\n<Shopkeeper>Understood~. I'll take your order~...

\n<\N[5]>(This guy... not only added extra eggs for
himself, but also ordered a bento...)

\n<Minato>Hehe, it's been a while since I had beef
bowl♪

\n<\N[5]>(Sigh... That's unfair. If you show me that
expression, I won't be able to say
anything...)

parameters:
\n<Minato>Thank you for the meal♪ I feel bad for having
you buy souvenirs for me.

\n<\N[5]>(That's something you ordered on your own,
right? Well, um... never mind...)

\n<\N[5]>(......Isn't this the perfect timing? It's hard to
deny that you're using food as
bait...but I'll just turn a blind eye to
that.)

\n<Minato>Thank you for today. Well then, see you at
the next street live...
\n<\N[5]>...Wait a minute!

I called out to Minato from behind. My
voice might have gotten a little louder.

\n<Minato>What...? I won't return this bento now, of all
times...

\n<\N[5]>I won't do such a thing! No, that's not
it...

\n<\N[5]>*cough*... Excuse me. I've been silent until now,
but I am this kind of person...

Handing her the business card that I couldn't
give her at that time.
\n<Minato>Onomichi... Production?
\n<\N[5]>...Neon Minato-san. I...came here to scout you.

I want to deliver your song to the
world...  Let me... no, allow me to help
you with that!
\n<\N[5]>(Uwaaaaaahhhhh! I bit itttttt!)
\n<Minato>Please give it to me...
\n<\N[5]>Please give it to me...

No, maybe it was too familiar... I got
scared at the last moment and ended up
changing direction while talking, which
turned out to be a disaster. It was a
carefully rehearsed, special line...

\n<Minato>No... There's also the possibility of
dialect...
\n<\N[5]>Well then, in that direction...
\n<Minato>Pfft... There's no way that's true.

\n<\N[5]>(Ku... This person... I endured the
embarrassment and tried to help, but
they betrayed me in seconds...)
\n<Minato>Well then... Thank you for today.

Minato waved her hand lightly and disappeared
into the station building with a quick
run.

Her response was Give me time. Well, that's
understandable. She's still a student
and has plenty of options for the
future. It's not easy for someone to
make a quick decision to live based on
their skills.
\n<\N[5]>(......I guess I'll wait for a message for now)

Finally, I felt relieved by the progress that
had been made, but deep down, I was
anxious. The business trip period of one
year in this town was coming to an end
in less than a month.

\n<\N[5]>(Maybe I've been too cautious... No, that's
not it. This... must be... unacceptable
as a scout...)

... I think I was simply enjoying the small
amount of time spent with her.  I was
afraid of losing that precious time.
The feeling of loss that was born in my
heart... maybe that's what it is.

As the time approaches when I have to
consider the handover, my free time to
move around is being reduced day by day.

Still, somehow managing my time, I headed
towards the station square, but since
that day... from the corner of the
square, which is her usual spot, only
her figure was conspicuously missing.

\n<\N[5]>(She's not here today... Did something happen?
If only I had asked for her contact
information...)

I might have been a little too
optimistic. I had assumed that I would
receive some kind of contact right away.
I'm disgusted with my own shallowness,
being satisfied with just handing over
my business card.

\n<\N[5]>(No... Maybe this is her answer. Perhaps I got
too close and scared her...)

......I looked out over the station square
without her. And then... there were two
men who seemed to be band members
setting up for a street live in that
space.

I couldn't bear the sight of that
everyday scene, as if she had never been
there from the beginning. I left the
square as if escaping...

Last night, I had a small farewell party and
ended up drinking a little too much, so
now I'm being attacked by a slight
headache.

\n<\N[5]>(Sigh... Should I buy some headache medicine on
the way?)

I finished all the handover tasks and was
able to successfully complete my
business trip. Today and tomorrow are
completely off, so all I have to do is
go home. I ended up indulging in a lazy
sleep until the afternoon.

\n<\N[5]>(It's been a year... It feels like it went by
in an instant...)

I look up at the hotel that took care of
me for a year and mutter in my heart.
\n<\N[5]>...Well, I guess I'll go home.

I'll head towards the main street. Usually,
I would take the bus when going to the
station, but today I want to walk while
indulging in sentimentality.

And then... as I walked confidently, a bus
passed me and stopped at the bus stop
ahead of my gaze.

\n<\N[5]>(If I run, will I make it? No, I've decided
to walk...)

I firmly decided to see off the bus and
continued walking. However, the bus
didn't depart at all, and the distance
between me and the bus was getting
closer.

\n<\N[5]>(Hmph... I know. If I run, the doors will close
right before I reach them, and I'll end
up in an awkward situation where I have
to ask the passengers to open the doors
again! I won't fall for that trick!)

\n<In-car announcement>We will be stopping for about 1 minute for
time adjustment. Please wait a moment.
\n<\N[5]>(Ah, I'll get on)... Hm...

On a Saturday afternoon, the square was
quite lively, and I walked through it,
looking around.
\n<\N[5]>(Is it feminine... but...)

......I want to meet Minato. Even if I'm being
avoided, I at least want to greet them.

However... Minato was nowhere to be seen, not even
in the usual spot in the square. It's
disappointing that I couldn't greet
them, but I won't be discouraged.
Because I'm sure we'll meet in the near
future.

\n<\N[5]>(Even if I don't do anything, Minato should
be able to be found by someone. And
then, in front of the TV... No, maybe
someone from my family will even co-
star...)

At that time, I apologized briefly and
left the square with a peaceful feeling,
hoping that we could have a chat about
old times...

I heard the sound of a message
notification coming from the bag hanging
on my shoulder.

\n<\N[5]>(I have to put down my bag to take out my
work smartphone, so maybe I should check
it on the train...)
\n<\N[5]>(Persistent... This sound must be a message, right?)
\n<\N[5]>Ah, excuse me...

I almost bumped into someone and
apologized. They were playing with their
smartphone while walking, so there was
no need for me to apologize...
\n<\N[5]>(Ugh, so persistent! Is it a prank message?!)

I set down my belongings on the seat that
was installed in the corridor, and took
out my smartphone.

\n<\N[5]>(Who is this... It's an unfamiliar email
address...)
......I check the received emails one by one.
Where are you right now, ?
Hey, .
Ah, you're here.
\n<\N[5]>(Huh... No way, what is this? It's scary...)
\n<\N[5]>L-Let's pretend we didn't see anything...

\n<？？？>Don't do it, and don't put away your
smartphone!

Suddenly, I was called out and unintentionally
let out a voice. With fear, I turned
around, and there... she was.
\n<Minato>Wh-What the heck! What do you mean by... me?
\n<\N[5]>...Neon? No, look at this...

I turned my smartphone towards her and
showed her the received emails one by
one.

\n<Minato>Eh... scary... Wait, isn't this the email I
sent!
\n<\N[5]>\{, is that you?! How confusing!
\n<Minato>By the way, 'Eek!?'
\n<\N[5]>Don't say it...
\n<Minato>Alright, then let's go.
\n<\N[5]>Are you going... with that luggage?

A large suitcase was placed at Minato's
feet.

\n<Minato>Hey... Don't play dumb now. I won't let you
pretend like nothing happened...

\n<\N[5]>No way... Are you planning to come with
me?

\n<Minato>Ah, that's my intention. I quit school and
my part- time job for that purpose, and
I even moved out of my house and
convinced my parents. It was tough...

\n<\N[5]>No no no no... Before that, couldn't you
have at least contacted me once...
\n<Minato>I thought I'd surprise you♪

......I was at a loss for words. Various
emotions overwhelmed me, and I didn't
have time to feel the joy of our
reunion.

\n<\N[5]>There are many complaints I want to make...
but why is today the day you're coming
back...

\n<Minato>I heard from the staff at Onomichi
Productions, so it's definitely decided,
right? Oh, make sure to come up with a
suitable story later, pretending to be
my girlfriend.

It's not that big of a production. Her story
must have already spread within the
company...

\n<\N[5]>I understand... Well, that's enough... By
the way, do you have a place to stay
over there?

\n<Minato>Until I find a place to live, take care of
me♪ Come on, let's go!
\n<\N[5]>Hey, wait a minute! What the... hey, Minato!

And so... And so... As spring comes to an
end and the cherry blossoms begin to
turn green, our story began with the
arrival of summer----...
